In article <1992Jan27.035506.5337@ryn.mro4.dec.com> jroth@allvax.enet.dec.com (Jim Roth) writes:
>But I haveen't seen the paper you cite; can you give an example of
>one of their generators?


These generators are chain-addition PRNGs with carry (or subtraction with
borrow).

	ranno = ( x[c[i+1]], carry[i+1] ) = x[a[i]] + x[b[i]] + carry[i]

	a[i], b[i], c[i] loop, modulo the length of an array.

	The period is close to 2^(# of bits in the array).
